UnitProtocolTimelock::constructor
├── when admin is zero address
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_ZeroAddress
├── when proposer is zero address
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_ZeroAddress
├── when executor is zero address
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_ZeroAddress
└── when all params are valid
    ├── it grants DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE to admin
    ├── it grants PROPOSER_ROLE to proposer
    ├── it grants CANCELLER_ROLE to proposer
    └── it grants EXECUTOR_ROLE to executor


UnitProtocolTimelock::queue
├── when caller lacks proposer role
│   └── it reverts
├── when operation is already queued
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_AlreadyQueued
└── when all conditions are met
    ├── it stores executeAfter as block timestamp plus MIN_DELAY
    ├── it returns the operation id
    └── it emits OperationQueued


UnitProtocolTimelock::execute
├── when caller lacks executor role
│   └── it reverts
├── when operation is not queued
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_NotQueued
├── when delay has not elapsed
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_NotReady
├── when call to target fails
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_ExecutionFailed
└── when all conditions are met
    ├── it deletes the operation
    ├── it calls target with data
    └── it emits OperationExecuted


UnitProtocolTimelock::cancel
├── when caller lacks canceller role
│   └── it reverts
├── when operation is not queued
│   └── it reverts with ProtocolTimelock_NotQueued
└── when operation is queued
    ├── it deletes the operation
    └── it emits OperationCancelled
